   <body>
      <p>The Document panel allows you to view all clauses and fields in your agreement document
            which can be edited. These clauses and fields are marked as smart clauses and
                smart fields in the document template from which the document was generated. </p>
      <note type="note">
         <p>Unless explicitly stated, any mention in this guide of fields or
                clauses should be considered a reference to smart fields and clauses.</p>
      </note>
      <p>To use the Document Panel, hover over the <image placement="inline"
                width="20"
                href="../attachments/45220125/49676341.png"
                id="image_xhb_lpn_12c"/>Document icon
         in the X-Author pane to display two menu choices: Fields and Clauses.</p>
      <fig id="fig_btn_mpn_12c">
         <image height="250"
                placement="break"
                width="277"
                href="../attachments/45220125/49676342.png"
                id="image_ctn_mpn_12c"/>
      </fig>
      <p>Based on your selection, the Document panel shows either the Fields or
                Clauses view. You can use the Document Panel to:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>View changed fields and clauses.</li>
         <li>Modify field values.</li>
         <li>Reject changes to clause content.</li>
         <li>Reject changes to field values.</li>
         <li>Validate values of changed fields.</li>
         <li>Mark clauses for deletion or undelete a clause.</li>
         <li>Unmark marked clauses.</li>
      </ul>
